    <note type="biography">
        <p>Swiss-born bryologist and palaeontologist. Moved to the United States in 1848; after brief periods assisting Louis Agassiz and Asa Gray, settled in Columbus, Ohio, where he assisted the bryologist William Starling Sullivant. Employed on geological surveys in the mid-western United States and Pennsylvania. Engaged by Agassiz to organise the palaeobotanical collections at the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard University, 1867–72.</p></note>
